cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DL, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the diffusion of ideas on Twitter, which is a social network platform. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper involves data scraping and analysis of a large dataset. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another possible category as the paper investigates the social dynamics of Twitter users and their interactions. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper involves analyzing a large amount of text data from Twitter. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper involves analyzing the popularity of topics on Twitter, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval.
